8677	  Let \(C^\bullet, C'^\bullet\) be cochain complexes in a preadditive category, with augmentation
8678	  maps \(f : Y \to C^0\) (\(f \cdot d^0 = 0\)) and \(f' : Y' \to C'^0\) (\(f' \cdot d'^0 = 0\)).
8679	  Given an isomorphism \(\varphi : C^\bullet \cong C'^\bullet\) of the base complexes, an
8680	  isomorphism \(e_Y : Y \cong Y'\) of the augmentation objects, and a compatibility square
8681	  \(f \cdot \varphi_0 = e_Y \cdot f'\) intertwining the augmentation maps through \(e_Y\) and the
8682	  degree-\(0\) component \(\varphi_0\) of \(\varphi\), there is an isomorphism of augmented
8683	  cochain complexes
8684	  \[
8685	    C^\bullet.\operatorname{augment} f \;\cong\; C'^\bullet.\operatorname{augment} f'.
8686	  \]
8687	\end{lemma}
8688	\begin{proof}
8689	  Define the isomorphism degreewise: take the degree-\(0\) component to be \(e_Y\) and the
8690	  degree-\(n+1\) component to be \(\varphi_n\), the \(n\)-th component of \(\varphi\). The
8691	  degree-\(0\) differential square is exactly the supplied compatibility square
8692	  \(f \cdot \varphi_0 = e_Y \cdot f'\). For each degree \(n+1\), the augmented differential is the
8693	  original differential of the base complex (the augmentation only modifies the bottom slot), so
8694	  the square reduces to the commutativity condition of \(\varphi\) at degree \(n\). Hence all squares commute and the components assemble to an isomorphism.
8695	\end{proof}
